# mechanical keyboard picks
#
# current daily driver:
# - logitech g610 orion (cherry mx brown, white led, dedicated media keys)
#   bus 003 device 011: id 046d:c338 logitech, inc. gaming keyboard g610
#
# discontinued. notes here are for picking a replacement when it dies.


# what i actually like about the g610

# - no rgb
# - minimal backlight — just white
# - dedicated multimedia controls (mute, play, prev, next, volume roller)
# - cherry mx brown switches
# - full-size layout (numpad available even if rarely used)
# - wired connection (no battery, no bluetooth pairing, no surprises)


# what i could give up

# - the numpad. could likely live with a 75% / tkl.
# - tradeoff: most tkl / 75% boards drop dedicated media keys to fn-layer.
#   only full-size "professional" boards still ship a real media row.
# - the backlight. don't actually need it. dropping this requirement opens
#   up the field considerably — most "serious professional" mechanical
#   boards skip backlight entirely, and availability is much better there.


# full-size replacements (matching all four criteria)

# the perfect fit:
# - das keyboard 6 pro
#   - cherry mx brown, white led only (no rgb), dedicated media row +
#     clickable volume knob, aluminum top, usb-c.
#   - essentially "the g610 made by a company that cares about looking
#     professional instead of gamer."
#   - lowest mental adjustment from current setup.

# compromise on one criterion:
# - das keyboard 4 professional
#   - drop the backlight; keep everything else.
#   - best-in-class media keys with the massive volume knob das is known for.
#   - the "if you don't actually need backlight" pick.
#
# - leopold fc900r pd (white led)
#   - drop dedicated media keys (fn-layer only).
#   - highest-build-quality keyboard on this list. korean-made, pbt keycaps
#     that won't shine like abs. "boring professional" aesthetic.
#   - the long-term-survivor pick.
#
# - varmilo va108m (white led)
#   - drop dedicated media keys (fn-layer).
#   - widest range of beautiful themed keycap sets, pbt keycaps. same build
#     philosophy as leopold.
#
# - keychron k10 pro (white led variant)
#   - drop dedicated media keys (volume knob + fn-layer media).
#   - hot-swappable switches (try different switches without buying a new
#     board). hybrid wired/wireless — works fine wired but you're paying for
#     a wireless module + battery you'll never use.
#   - the future-proofing pick if you accept the hybrid tax.


# full-size, NO BACKLIGHT (best availability tier)

# dropping the backlight requirement opens up the "serious professional"
# segment, where availability is much better than the white-led niche.

# the dedicated-media-row pick:
# - das keyboard 4 professional
#   - cherry mx brown, no backlight, dedicated media row + massive volume
#     knob, full-size, usb.
#   - essentially "the g610 minus backlight." in production for 10+ years.
#   - usually findable on daskeyboard.com direct or amazon.
#   - best fit if dedicated media keys are non-negotiable.

# accept fn-layer media keys (field opens up considerably):
# - filco majestouch 2 (full-size)
#   - the canonical "boring professional" mechanical. cherry mx brown, no
#     backlight, no media keys (fn+f-keys), pbt keycaps on some variants.
#   - best availability on this entire list. reliably stocked at
#     mechanicalkeyboards.com and amazon. 15+ years as the typist default.
#
# - filco majestouch 3 (full-size)
#   - newer usb-c version, same dna, also reliably stocked.
#
# - leopold fc900r (non-pd)
#   - cherry mx brown, no backlight, pbt keycaps standard, no media keys.
#   - better availability than the white-led pd variant since fewer people
#     specifically want leds.
#   - korean build quality — arguably highest on this list.
#
# - varmilo va108m (non-backlit)
#   - cherry mx brown, pbt, very wide selection of themed keycap sets.
#   - direct from varmilo.com.
#
# - ikbc cd108
#   - cherry mx, pbt, no backlight. cheaper than filco / leopold.
#   - sometimes available via amazon third-party.

# hot-swap option (give up dedicated media row):
# - keychron q6 barebones / non-backlit sku
#   - full-size, hot-swap, dedicated knob (not full media row), no backlight
#     on the right sku. best long-term flexibility but no dedicated media row.


# bonus benefit of going filco / leopold / varmilo: pbt keycaps standard

# the g610 has abs keycaps that slowly develop a glossy shine on the most-
# used keys (wasd, e, r, t, space, enter) after 1-2 years of daily use.
# pbt keycaps don't do that — they keep their texture indefinitely. real
# upgrade that comes for free with the "professional" segment.


