# important tradeoffs

# dedicated media keys disappear at tkl. almost all tkl / 75% boards put
# media on an fn-layer (fn+f7/f8/f9 etc.) rather than dedicated buttons.
# the g610's standalone volume roller + media row is one of the things you
# give up with the smaller form factor. solvable with a small dedicated
# macropad or a knob like the 8bitdo retro mechanical knob that just does
# media.
#
# white-led-only boards are harder to find than they should be. most
# "premium mechanical" makers ship rgb by default and treat white-led as an
# afterthought. you have to specifically hunt the white-led sku.
#
# availability is real: the strict white-led + no-rgb + cherry mx + media
# keys combo has been squeezed out by the market split between "rgb gaming"
# (corsair, razer, logitech) and "enthusiast no-backlight" (custom builds,
# hot-swap pcbs). das and leopold's white-led skus are often out of stock.
# dropping the backlight requirement (no-backlight section above) gives
# significantly better availability.
#
# arrow cluster on 75% boards: the loss of arrow-cluster spacing on some
# 75% boards bothers people more than they expect. try one in a store
# before committing. tkl is the safer first step away from full-size.
#
# wired vs hybrid: das, leopold, varmilo are all wired-by-default — no
# tax for the wired preference. keychron's k / q series are hybrid
# wired/wireless (you pay for the wireless module + battery even if you
# never use them). if wired-only matters, drop to keychron's c-series
# (wired only, cheaper), or just plug in a k-series and ignore the
# bluetooth.


# the recommendations

# want "my g610 but slightly nicer" (white backlight, dedicated media row):
# → das 6 pro. same ergonomics, same feature set, better materials.
#   availability caveat: buy from daskeyboard.com direct; amazon listings
#   are spotty.
#
# want dedicated media row, don't need backlight:
# → das keyboard 4 professional. same feature set as the 6 pro minus the
#   backlight, has been in production for 10+ years, more reliably stocked.
#
# want "best-built full-size mechanical i can buy" (don't mind fn-layer media):
# → leopold fc900r pd (white led) or leopold fc900r (no backlight). pbt
#   keycaps + korean build quality. the no-backlight variant has better
#   availability than the pd.
#
# want maximum availability + boring professional vibe:
# → filco majestouch 2 or 3. no backlight, no media row, but reliably in
#   stock at mechanicalkeyboards.com and amazon. 15+ years as the typist
#   default for a reason.
#
# want future-proofing (swap switches later):
# → keychron q6 (hot-swap, full-size, give up media row). or keychron k10 pro
#   white-led with the hybrid wired/wireless tax.
#
# the das 6 pro and das 4 professional are the only ones with a dedicated
# media row exactly like the g610. if those buttons are non-negotiable,
# that narrows it to two.
#
# wired-only doesn't materially change the top picks: das, leopold, varmilo,
# filco are all wired-by-default. keychron is the only brand where you pay
# a hybrid wired/wireless tax.
